ciently radiating, shocks. This suggests that mapping such shock\nstructures in the ICM in a cluster's outskirts (via e.g. radio synchrotron\nemission) could provide a complementary measure of its recent merger and\naccretion history.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Oct 2018 05:30:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 14 Nov 2019 23:45:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-18"}
